Yep, like I thought: 
<a href="https://github.com/YCSRobotics/SwerveBot-2024-Robot/blob/f8056122b44ae258a807c6d6c9315053db12ab60/src/main/java/frc/robot/RobotContainer.java#L58" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">Here</a> you’re creating a Trigger every loop. There’s a known bug there that leads to loop overruns. 
Create the trigger once, and pass it as a BooleanSupplier (Triggers are BooleanSuppliers): 
-            () -&gt; m_driver.leftBumper().getAsBoolean()));
+          m_driver.leftBump&hellip;
